<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2777</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-27T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            27, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>276. Your September 23, 12 p.m., No. 420, received. The Government of
                                the United States has never recognized the Bolshevik authorities and
                                does not consider that its efforts to safeguard supplies at
                                Archangel or to help the Czechs in Siberia have created a state of
                                war with the Bolsheviki.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>